      "raw_text": "ut may be possible this year to\ncut the tax levy from 80 to %\nmills\" stated Assessor E. P. Gal\nbraith this morning, \"if the city\nwill increase the saloon license\nfrom 5000 to $1,000 year, thereby\nadding about $4,000 to its income.\nWith this and the increased valua-\nton of all property, l believe the\nreduction can be made\"\n\n\nThe board of equalization finished\nits work Saturday night. The ex-\nact levy will not be decided until\nthe first meeting OF the board of\ncounty commissioners in October."
